cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE

This paper is about natural language processing and specifically focuses on parsing UCCA semantic graphs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves classification models, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with data statistics and training frameworks, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
